- The `OFFSET(...,3,3)` keeps the height (3 rows) and width (3 columns) of the original range.
- The rest of the formula (`INDEX(...,0,MATCH(...))`) remains unchanged, preserving the original sum‑and‑index/match functionality.

When this formula is placed in the first target cell and dragged down, the column reference will shift as required while the row references stay constant.

